settings.title: About us
settings.text:
J&K Aquatics was formed in 1984, by Paul and Judy James, initially as a part time venture with a small retail shop in Wellington. Over the intervening years they have built the company into one of the UK’s largest wholesalers of aquatic dry goods and fish, serving the whole of the UK and ROI.

In 2013, J&K Aquatics moved to a 2.3-acre site with a purpose-built warehouse, fish house and office facilities, just off the motorway at junction 24, North Petherton.

These new premises allowed J&K Aquatics to hold more stock and their continued investment in technology to improve their service means that their logistics and processes are more streamlined than ever. They can get products onto the shelves in your store faster than ever before and their operation ensures that they offer a reliable supply of products and an accurate service.

At J&K Aquatics they aim to provide a complete aquatic service, offering their customers access to a comprehensive selection of core brands and commodity items covered by their Betta range, as well as specialist lines imported from around the world.

They have created a one-stop shop for all your aquatic needs as they also offer quality fish and plants, saving you time when ordering. All of this is backed up by competitive pricing and the highest standards of service and support.

J&K Aquatics pride themselves on being a unique wholesaler that can provide livestock and dry goods on one order. They continue to refine and improve the warehouse and fishhouse to make sure they offer the best and most varied supply.

Alongside their vast range of tropical species, they wholesale a range of marine fish, invertebrates, and more!

Their coldwater offering is also expanding on a weekly basis and they are continuing to develop this area. A real focus has been put on finding exciting species that will provide a real draw to get customers through your doors.

The past few years has seen some real changes in our industry with customers changing their ordering behaviour, and many manufacturers reviewing their route to market. J&K Aquatics however, is an agile business, willing to adapt to the changes its' customers face whilst keeping its' core values of providing an honest, reliable service at its' heart.

settings.question: How do I set up an account with J&K Aquatics?
settings.answer: If you’d like to set up an account with us, please register via Trade Account Register

settings.question: Does J&K Aquatics sell to the public?
settings.answer: J&K Aquatics is a wholesaler and deals only with trade customers. We do not sell directly to the public but we are more than happy to point you in the direction of your nearest stockist.

settings.question: I do not have retail premises, can I open an account?
settings.answer: We do not open accounts with anyone intending to sell our products if they do not have retail premises. However, we will open accounts for universities and public aquaria for the consumption and use of our products.

settings.question: Do I need a pet shop licence to open an account?
settings.answer:
Any Pet Shops selling animals in England, Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland require a Pet Shop licence and we ask that you provide a copy of it when you open an account with us. For customers who do not carry livestock (garden centres, hardware stores etc.) this is not a requirement.

For advice on applying for a pet shop licence please visit www.gov.uk/pet-shop-licence. For customers in Northern Ireland please visit www.gov.co.uk/pet-shop-licence-northern-ireland. Pet Shop licences are not currently issued in the Republic of Ireland.

settings.question: What is the minimum order to qualify for delivery?
settings.answer: The minimum order value is £425 (+VAT) in England and Wales. It is £500 (+VAT) for dry goods and £325 (+VAT) for livestock in Scotland/Some Northern English Counties. It is £500 (+VAT) in Northern Ireland and it is £500 (+VAT) for the Republic of Ireland.

settings.question: Can I receive a delivery if I don’t meet the minimum order?
settings.answer: Depending on the location of your business, you may be able to receive your delivery through a courier and an additional carriage fee will be applied.

settings.question: Do fish count as part of the minimum order?
settings.answer: Yes, if the order is being delivered to England and Wales.

settings.question: When does my order need to be in by?
settings.answer: Orders must be placed by midday on the designated order day for your area. Please contact your rep or get in touch with our sales office by phone on 01278 664488 or by email at sales@jnk-aquatics.co.uk to find out what day we take orders from your area.

settings.question: What delivery schedule am I on?
settings.answer: Depending on the location of your business, you will receive your orders on different days. If you are unsure what your scheduled delivery day is please contact your rep or get in touch with our sales office by phone on 01278 664488 or by email at sales@jnk-aquatics.co.uk.

settings.question: Part of my delivery is missing, what should I do?
settings.answer: Please contact our sales office by phone on 01278 664488 or by email at sales@jnk-aquatics.co.uk within 24 hours of delivery to report any discrepancies.

settings.question: There are breakages or damaged products on my delivery, what should I do?
settings.answer:
Please contact our sales office by phone on 01278 664488 or by email at sales@jnk-aquatics.co.uk within 24 hours of delivery to report any damaged or broken products.

Any larger items, including aquariums or cabinets, must be checked with the driver at the time of delivery, we ask that you sign for its safe receipt at this point.

settings.question: Can fish be delivered to my location?
settings.answer: We deliver livestock to most areas of the UK and some parts of Ireland. Please contact us to find out if fish can be delivered to your store.

settings.question: I’m based in ROI; can I order cold water fish?
settings.answer:
We can deliver some species of cold-water fish to the Republic of Ireland. To obtain the correct certification, they must be ordered a week in advance to allow for an on-site inspection by DEFRA and will require completed import documentation from you. Please contact our fish house on 01278 661918 or at fishhouse@jnk-aquatics.co.uk for more information regarding this process.

In order to import livestock into Ireland, you have to register as a livestock importer with the Irish government. You can read more about that here: https://ireland.jnk-aquatics.co.uk/pages/licences

settings.question: Can I order Tortoises from J&K?
settings.answer: Yes, although stock is not held on our website. Please contact the fish house by phone on 01278 661918 or at fishhouse@jnk-aquatics.co.uk to enquire about Tortoises.

settings.question: When does my order need to be in by?
settings.answer:
Livestock orders must be placed by midday on the designated order day for your area.

Please contact your rep or our sales office by phone on 01278 664488 or by email at sales@jnk-aquatcs.co.uk to find out what day we take livestock orders from your area.

settings.question: Who do I contact about returns?
settings.answer: Please get in touch with us if you have any queries relating to returns by phone on 01278 664488 or by email at sales@jnk-aquatics.co.uk.

settings.question: My customer has returned an item but has lost their receipt, can I still return the product to J&K?
settings.answer: We require proof of purchase for all products returned to J&K. All manufacturers require a receipt to show that the product is still within warranty. For full details on this, please click here

settings.title: South West and Key Accounts
settings.subtitle: Justin Simmons
settings.text:
Justin has worked in sales for all of his working life and has been in the aquatic trade for over 10 years.

These roles allowed Justin to gain invaluable insight into how retailers from small independents to large multi nationals conduct their business and in particular have allowed him to develop his knowledge of effective selling to the end user.

Justin has developed a passion for aquascaping. He currently has an Eheim Incipria 330 which is fully aquascaped and is running Eheim’s new Digital products.

Email: justin.simmons@jnk-aquatics.co.uk

Phone: 07776172737

settings.title: North West and Midlands
settings.subtitle: Mark Reynolds
settings.text:
Mark started work in the aquatics trade at the age of 16 where he started work as a Sales Assistant in the aquatics department of his local pet store. From there Mark worked his way up to Deputy Manager gaining a good insight into the management of a busy pet store.

His role in territory management started in 2006 going onto join J&K Aquatics a year later.

His current position see him covering the Midlands, North Wales, North West and parts of the North East.

Mark’s main areas of expertise are in Freshwater aquatics and he is a keen aquascaper with both a 30l Nano planted Co2 aquarium and a 250L Amazonian setup.

Email: mark.reynolds@jnk-aquatics.co.uk

Phone: 07921888839

settings.title: Southeast, London, East Anglia, and The East Midlands
settings.subtitle: Scott Peck
settings.text:
Scott has 10 years of experience of working in aquatic retail.

First of all, he worked at an aquatic retailer in Croydon then he moved to the pet department of a garden centre in Surrey, which included indoor fish. Most recently he has worked as a retail koi specialist.

He has kept most types of fish and he has had many aquariums up to 6' x 2 x 2 tanks in his time.

His areas of interests include nanoscapes and aquascaping. 
He currently has a ADA cube fully planted and has a keen eye for Siamese fighters.

Email: scott.peck@jnk-aquatics.co.uk

Phone: 07990533923

settings.title: Northwest, North Wales, Scotland, and Ireland
settings.subtitle: Kris Gibbs
settings.text:
Kris has worked in sales for most of his career, starting in mobile phone sales and retail for ten years, before moving into aquatics. 

For the last five years he has been running an aquatic centre in North Wales, as well as building and maintaining ponds on a freelance basis. 

Kris has always wanted to spend time in Ireland, especially to travel in it and experience the beauty of the country.

Kris hopes to push J&K’s growth as well his own, personally and professionally. He works to establish positive relationships with all of J&K’s clients as well as continue to grow the numbers of clients he has.  He takes pride in becoming a valuable member of the team.

At home, Kris has a 60 litre planted tank with community fish, and is currently building a large koi pond in his garden.

Email: kris.gibbs@jnk-aquatics.co.uk

Phone: 07766008391
